incident_updates.body: We have new information regarding the incident that affected your service(s). Please find below an update on the situation: Update : Our teams are still working on the issue for the impacted customers. Ongoing Actions : The incident has been identified and our teams are mobilised to restore service as quickly as possible. We will keep you updated on the progress and resolution. We apologize for any inconvenience caused and appreciate your understanding.

We have new information regarding the incident that affected your service(s). Please find below an update on the situation: Update : Some customers are still experiencing a discrepancy between the actual size of their bucket and the size displayed in the Manager, due to undeleted parts that should have been removed. To address this issue, affected customers will receive an informational email and a credit note on their invoice, compensating for excess consumption, with credits applied as of April 18, 2025. Processing are completed in followings region: UK, TOR, SGP , SYD , MUM and US. Ongoing Actions : The incident has been identified and our technical teams are working to address the storage size of the impacted customers between those two dates on SBG, GRA, BHS, EU-WEST-PAR-A, EU-WEST-PAR-B and EU-WEST-PAR-C regions. We would also like to assure you that refunds are still being processed. We will keep you updated on the progress and resolution. We apologize for any inconvenience caused and appreciate your understanding.

We have determined the origin of the incident affecting our Object Storage offer. Here are some supplementary details : Start time : 25/03/2025 09:00 UTC Impacted Service(s) : Object storage offer degradation. Customers Impact : Between 25/03/2025 09:00 UTC and 18/04/2025 16:00 UTC, when customers deleting an object with MPU (only objects with more than 100 parts), only the first 100 parts were deleted. Since 18/04/2025 16:00 UTC, the bug is fixed and all parts are now correctly deleted. Because of this bug, customers will have a discrepancy between the actual bucket size and the size displayed in the Manager because of parts that not have been deleted but should have been. In the meantime, our technical teams are working on the storage size of the impacted customers between those 2 dates. Root Cause : This incident is caused by a software issue. Ongoing Actions : The incident has been identified and our teams are mobilised to restore service as quickly as possible. We will keep you updated on the progress and resolution. We apologize for any inconvenience caused and appreciate your understanding.

As part of our continuous improvement plan, maintenance is scheduled on our Virtual Private Servers offer. Start time : 04/07/2025 09:00 UTC End time : 04/08/2025 21:00 UTC Service impact : Below-mentioned images will no longer be available to purchase or use. Several images currently offered as part of our VPS offering have reached, or are approaching, End of Life (EoL). As of August 4th, 2025, these images will be officially removed from our VPS catalog in accordance with our End of Life policy. You can read more about our distribution End of Life policy here : https://help.ovhcloud.com/csm/en-gb-public-cloud-compute-vps-image-life-cycle?id=kb_article_view&sysparm_article=KB0050801 Below is the complete list of images, as well our recommendations and alternatives for VPS environments.

You can refer to the following guides to : Upgrade operating system: https://help.ovhcloud.com/csm/en-gb-public-cloud-compute-upgrade-operating-system?id=kb_article_view&sysparm_article=KB0051306 Upload your image: https://help.ovhcloud.com/csm/en-gb-public-cloud-compute-upload-own-image?id=kb_article_view&sysparm_article=KB0051319 Service improvement : As part of our End of Life policy, the above-mentioned images will no longer be available for purchase or reinstallation in our VPS offering. For any question, please reach out to our support team. Thank you for your understanding.
